@startuml hvac_stale_input_to_comfort_error_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title HVAC Stale Input To Comfort Error Signal Flow\n(TMU/HVAC/vehicle freshness -> BCM -> comfort error publication)

participant "TMU / HVAC /\nvehicle freshness" as FreshnessCtx #F4F7FB
participant "BCM\ncomfort owner" as BCM #E8F7E8
participant "Comfort state bus" as ComfortBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers / panels /\nevidence" as Obs #E8F0FE

== Freshness Check ==

FreshnessCtx -> BCM : gTmuServiceRxMs\ngHvacStateRxMs\ngVehicleRxMs
BCM -> BCM : tmuInputStale = recentTick(TMU) ? 0 : 1
BCM -> BCM : hvacInputStale = recentTick(HVAC) ? 0 : 1
BCM -> BCM : vehicleCtxInputStale = recentTick(vehicle) ? 0 : 1
note right of BCM
Representative freshness gates
- tmuInputStale
- hvacInputStale
- vehicleCtxInputStale
end note

== Comfort Error Ownership ==

BCM -> BCM : if any stale input is active\nthen comfortError = 1
BCM -> BCM : if vehicle/door/seat detail stale\nthen comfortProfile = 0
BCM -> ComfortBus : frmBodyComfortStateMsg\nComfortProfile / ComfortStatus / ComfortError
note right of BCM
Representative outputs
- ComfortProfile
- ComfortStatus
- ComfortError
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

ComfortBus -> Obs : comfort readback /\nstale-state evidence

note over FreshnessCtx, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. BCM evaluates TMU, HVAC, and vehicle-context freshness
2. BCM suppresses comfort profile when stale context exists
3. BCM raises ComfortError on the body comfort publication path
4. Panels and evidence consumers observe degraded comfort service state
end note

@enduml
